Data Types : It is data type that determines which type of data we can store inside of a variable.
There are two types of data type :
1) Primitive data types
2) Non-Primitive data types

1) Primitive data types : a) byte - stores integer type value - upto 1 byte i.e 8 bit
                          b) short - stores integer type value - upto 2 byte i.e 16 bit
                          c) int - stores integer type value - upto 4 byte i.e 32 bit
                          d) long - stores integer type value - upto 8 byte i.e 64 bit
                          e) float - stores floating point i.e. decimal point values - upto 4 byte i.e. 32 bit
                          f) double - stores floating point i.e. decimal point values - more precise - upto 8 byte i.e. 64 bit
                          g) char - stores single character, symbol using single quotes (e.g. 'a','@',etc) - upto 2 byte i.e 16 bit
                          h) boolean - stores true or false - 1 bit
                          
